    "course_title": "TEACHING WORLD LANGUAGES (K-8)",
    "description": "Designed for future teachers of world languages to build their philosophy of education and philosophy of teaching in conjunction with building practical knowledge about teaching and learning, professional standards, and issues facing schools. Provides opportunities to apply theories and standards through the practice of planning for language and child development through the creation of lesson plans, unit plans, and assessment creation. Pass oral proficiency exam, concurrent enrollment inCURRIC\u00a0243, and declared in French, German, or Spanish BSE",
